review_blob:
Smells of light coffee aroma. Not too heavy. Pours with a lighter brown head. Strong coffee flavor which overshadows the rest of the flavors. Good coffee stout.

Strong chocolate presence including the aroma. Sharp taste up front followed by a very distinct but quality chocolate taste. Not a bad chocolate beer. Prefer Duclaw Cocoa Retribution over this beer for a chocolate experience.

Had this on tap at Always Rons in Hagerstown, MD. Spice aroma is strong. Bitter after taste but full of flavor. Very 'bitey'. Pumpkin is not too apparent. This is an okay beer.
